Description: Tests for slope homogeneity in panel quantile regression models. 
    Implements the S-hat statistic (chi-squared asymptotics for fixed n, large T) 
    and the D-hat statistic (standard normal asymptotics for large n and T) 
    proposed by Galvao, Juhl, Montes-Rojas, and Olmo (2017) 
    <doi:10.1093/jjfinec/nbx027>. Computes minimum distance quantile regression 
    estimators that optimally combine individual panel estimates under slope 
    homogeneity. Supports both joint tests across all coefficients and marginal 
    tests for individual variables. Includes bandwidth selection methods 
    (Hall-Sheather and Bofinger) and optional HAC variance estimation for 
    dependent data.
